label.value: decreased response to mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint signaling

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which a mitotic cell cycle arrest that normally occurs in response to the mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint is decreased. The mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint normally delays the metaphase/anaphase transition of a mitotic nuclear division until the spindle is correctly assembled and chromosomes are attached to the spindle. In a mutant, the checkpoint may fail to arrest or delay cell cycle progression under appropriate conditions, or the incidence or duration of arrest or delay may differ from wild type under any specified set of conditions.

label.value: decreased duration of mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint

value.value: A cell cycle checkpoint phenotype in which the duration of cell cycle arrest or delay due to regulation by the mitotic spindle assembly checkpoint is lower than in wild type.

label.value: decreased mitotic checkpoint complex level

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells contain fewer mitotic checkpoint complexes than normal.

label.value: normal mitotic checkpoint complex assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitotic checkpoint complex assembly is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased extent and duration of protein-protein interaction

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the binding of one protein to another occurs to a lower extent, and for a shorter time, than normal. The relevant proteins may include the one encoded by the mutated gene, or may both be encoded by different genes.

definition.value: This term can be used for any protein-protein interaction that is affected by a mutation, whether or not the mutated gene product is one of the interacting proteins. We recommend noting which proteins were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased duration of protein-protein interaction

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the binding of one protein to another occurs for a shorter time than normal. The relevant proteins may include the one encoded by the mutated gene, or may both be encoded by different genes.

definition.value: This term can be used for any protein-protein interaction that is affected by a mutation, whether or not the mutated gene product is one of the interacting proteins. We recommend noting which proteins were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased spatial extent of double-strand break processing

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which double-strand break processing extends for a shorter distance from the breaks site than normal. Double-strand break processing is the 5' to 3' exonucleolytic resection of the DNA at the site of the break to form a 3' single-strand DNA overhang.

label.value: normal spatial extent of double-strand break processing

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which double-strand break processing extends for a normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) distance from the break site. Double-strand break processing is the 5' to 3' exonucleolytic resection of the DNA at the site of the break to form a 3' single-strand DNA overhang.

label.value: increased gene conversion during vegetative growth

value.value: A DNA recombination phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which gene conversion occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: C-shaped vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is curved along the long axis to form a "C" shape. In a curved cell, the long axis follows a smooth bend rather than a straight line. In a C-shaped cell, the curve is centered at the midpoint of the long axis of the cell.

label.value: J-shaped vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is curved along the long axis to form a "J" shape. In a curved cell, the long axis follows a smooth bend rather than a straight line. In a J-shaped cell, the curve is centered away from the midpoint of the long axis of the cell.

label.value: abnormal shmoo directionality

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which a shmoo forms with normal morphology, but in an abnormal location.

label.value: T-shaped cell during G0 to G2 transition

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a new growth zone forms along the lateral portion of the cell (often in the middle) before septation, such that a single cell grows in the form of the letter T, when the cell undergoes transition from G0 phase to G2. Cell length is normal.

definition.value: Cells enter quiescence (G0) from G2 when starved for glucose, and can re-enter the cell cycle at G2 when glucose again becomes available. A T-shaped cell may septate perpendicular to the normal septation axis, and divide to form normal-shaped daughter cells. Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'viable cell population' (FYPO:0002058) or one of its descendants.

label.value: bent cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a cell is bent along the long axis. In a bent cell, the long axis has one or more angles, rather than following a straight line.

label.value: bent cell during G0 to G1 transition

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a cell is bent along the long axis when the cell undergoes transition from G0 phase to G1. In a bent cell, the long axis has one or more angles, rather than following a straight line.

definition.value: A T-shaped cell may septate perpendicular to the normal septation axis, and divide to form normal-shaped daughter cells. Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'viable cell population' (FYPO:0002058) or one of its descendants.

label.value: short disorganized microtubule bundle

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which microtubule bundles are shorter than normal and have an abnormal structure. Typically, microtubule bundles do not reach the cell tips and are not aligned parallel to the long axis of the cell.

label.value: short microtubule bundle

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which microtubule bundles are shorter than normal.

label.value: decreased protein localization to cell cortex of cell tip during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell cortex of one or both cell tips is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased microtubule dwell time at cell tip

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which microtubule plus ends remain in contact with the cell cortex at cell tips for a shorter time than normal.

label.value: abnormal protein movement within plasma membrane during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the movement of one or more proteins within the plasma membrane is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased rate of protein movement within plasma membrane at cell tip

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the movement of one or more proteins within the plasma membrane of the cell tip occurs more slowly than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased rate of protein movement within plasma membrane at cell tip

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the movement of one or more proteins within the plasma membrane of the cell tip occurs more quickly than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased rate of protein movement within plasma membrane at cell side

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the movement of one or more proteins within the plasma membrane of the lateral part of the cell occurs more slowly than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein movement within plasma membrane during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the movement of one or more proteins within the plasma membrane is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal rate of protein movement within plasma membrane at cell tip

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of movement of one or more proteins within the plasma membrane of the cell tip is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal rate of protein movement within plasma membrane at cell side

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of movement of one or more proteins within the plasma membrane of the lateral part of the cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein movement within plasma membrane

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the movement of one or more proteins within the plasma membrane is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal rate of protein movement within spore plasma membrane

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the rate, or speed, of movement of one or more proteins within the plasma membrane of a spore is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: short astral microtubules

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells form astral microtubules that are shorter than normal.

label.value: T-shaped cell during recovery from quiescence

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a new growth zone forms along the lateral portion of the cell (often in the middle) before septation, such that a single cell grows in the form of the letter T, when the cell undergoes transition from G0 phase, re-entering the cell cycle phase from which it entered G0 (G1 or G2). Cell length is normal.

definition.value: A T-shaped cell may septate perpendicular to the normal septation axis, and divide to form normal-shaped daughter cells. Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'viable cell population' (FYPO:0002058) or one of its descendants.

label.value: abnormal nuclear membrane biogenesis involved in mitosis

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the biogenesis of nuclear membrane that normally forms part of mitosis is abnormal.

label.value: normal protein localization to microtubule end during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to one or both ends of a microtubule is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to microtubule plus-end

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the plus ends of microtubules does not occur.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to perinuclear region of cytoplasm during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the perinuclear region of the cytoplasm is abnormal during mitotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal microtubule-based movement

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which microtubule-based movement is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abolished protein localization to microtubule plus-end during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to one or both ends end of a microtubule does not occur during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein neddylation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the neddylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein neddylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the neddylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein neddylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of neddylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal NEDD8-specific protease activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of NEDD8-specific protease activity (deneddylase activity) is abnormal.

definition.value: Secreted invertase activity is usually measured.

label.value: decreased NEDD8-specific protease activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of NEDD8-specific protease activity (deneddylase activity) is decreased under conditions of glucose starvation.

label.value: increased phosphatidylserine externalization

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of phosphatidylserine measured in the outer leaflet of the plasma membrane is higher than normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Normally, phosphatidylserine is restricted to the inner leaflet of the plasma membrane.

definition.value: The appearance of phosphatidylserine on the external side of the plasma membrane is a marker for apoptosis.

label.value: increased plasma membrane permeability

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the permeability of the plasma membrane to one or more substances is greater than normal.

definition.value: Note that an abnormal plasma membrane organization process may, but does not necessarily, result in abnormal plasma membrane morphology.

label.value: sensitive to iron

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to iron ions. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of iron ions that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: decreased level of generation of precursor metabolites and energy gene mRNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more generation of precursor metabolites and energy RNAs measured in a cell is lower than normal (i.e. lower than observed in wild-type cells). Generation of precursor metabolites and energy RNAs are transcribed from genes whose products are involved in the formation of precursor metabolites and the liberation of energy from these substances.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: normal protein transport along microtubule during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein transport along microtubules is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein transport along microtubule to cell tip during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein transport along microtubules to the cell tip is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein transport along microtubule during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein transport along microtubules is abnormal. Transport of all proteins or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein transport along microtubule to cell tip during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein transport along microtubules to the cell tip is abnormal. Transport of all proteins or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein transport along microtubule to cell tip cortex during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which protein transport along microtubules to the cortex of the cell tip is abnormal. Transport of all proteins or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.
